content:
Lack of progress in Russia-Ukraine peace talks pushed oil prices higher and left stocks broadly lower.

Dow ends -65, -0.2% to 35,228. Nasdaq -1.2%, S&P -0.6%. Of 11 S&P stock sectors just four rose, led by energy, +1.2%.

US crude oil rose 3% to $107.33. Bond ylds eased further.

US crude oil rose 3% to $107.33. Bond ylds eased further.

content: It's an ironic fact that Russia's cold war against Ukraine has made its hot war far more difficult; by denying Ukraine access to its gas and oil reserves, Russia kept Ukraine poor, resulting in a low-grade road infrastructure that is gumming up Russian mobility during mud season.

content:
@TheSilverCloak @JeanPie24520 @RachelG21879460 EU is a single market for trade. It's EU that governs the trade policy for the whole of the EU. That's why I'm blaming the EU. Each member state can't govern over its own trade.

EU should ban Russian oil and gas imports to stop funding Russia's war in Ukraine. It's a sanction.

@suhasinih India depends: 
* On Ukraine for defence requirements.
* Ditto & more on Russia
* On America to counter China.
* On Iraq/Iran/UAE/US/S.Arabia for the bulk of  85% of our oil requirement
* On China for bulk drugs/electronics.

It's a bloody miracle we have a foreign policy at all.
